<p class="MsoNormal" align="center" style="text-align: center">
<font face="Tahoma" size="5"><b>Sharing 
content through XML</b></font></p>
<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;</p>
<ul>
  <li>
<p class="MsoNormal">These portals allow an XML representation of the stories to 
be served out.&nbsp; This allows for a truly distributed system.&nbsp; For example 
we can pull headlines in from other sites to display on ours.&nbsp; The content 
is updated dynamically.&nbsp; The schema is a defined web standard, the RDF 
format.&nbsp; My website uses a feed from the Slashdot news site.&nbsp; The XML 
file can be viewed here:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
<a href="http://slashdot.org/slashdot.rdf">rdf file for Slashdot</a></p>
  </li>
</ul>
